        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "In the current [todo list|http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/apidoc\/core\/todolist.html], there are three similar topics for the {{Zend_Controller_Request_Http}} about making available to retrieve values from nested arrays in the _GET, _POST and _COOKIE superglobals, via the _getQuery()_, _getPost()_ and _getCookie()_ methods. The solution I suggest is to also accept an array as the first parameter of each method, wich would have the sequence of keys to walk through the nested arrays.\n\n{code:title=Zend_Controller_Request_Http|borderStyle=solid}\n\n    public function getQuery($key = null, $default = null)\n    {\n        if (null === $key) {\n            return $_GET;\n        }\n        if (is_array($key)) {\n            $value = $_GET;\n            foreach ($key as $index) {\n                if (!isset($value[$index])) {\n                    return $default;\n                }\n                $value = $value[$index];\n            }\n            return $value;\n        }\n\n        return (isset($_GET[$key])) ? $_GET[$key] : $default;\n    }\n\n{code}"
        },
