                    "updated": "2008-09-15T14:54:41.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/25709",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "How hard is it really to simply pull the array and access it?\n{code}\n$get = $this->getQuery();\n$value = (isset($get['foo']['bar'])) ? $get['foo']['bar'] : $default;\n{code}\n\nI'm not sure I see a burning need for this functionality.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-11-05T12:06:44.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-11-05T12:06:44.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/45521",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=demonkoryu",
                        "name": "demonkoryu",
                        "displayName": "Tobias Hoffmann",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "It's a convenience method, and a cleaner way than descending through the array by yourself.\r\nIf this was coded in, it would be possible to use it in declarative ways:\r\n\r\n \/\/ fictional code: \r\n $dataKey = 'billing\/firstname'; \r\n $data = $request->getPost($dataKey);",
